title: NRL teams round 1 2017: team lists, squads, injuries, live | Gold Coast Bulletin
text:
LIVE: NRL teams round 1 2017 The Daily Telegraph REGISTER FOR SUPERCOACH NOW 
WELCOME to our live coverage of the round 1 NRL team announcements. 
Check out the full Round 1 NRL team lists plus expert SuperCoach analysis from Tom Sangster and Rikki-Lee Arnold. SHARKS V BRONCOS 
8:05pm AEDT Thursday, Southern Cross Group Stadium 
Sharks: 1. Gerard Beale 2. Sosaia Feki 3. Jack Bird 4. Ricky Leutele 5. Edrick Lee 6. James Maloney 7. Chad Townsend 8. Andrew Fifita 9. Jayden Brailey 10. Matt Prior 11. Luke Lewis 12. Wade Graham 13. Paul Gallen. Interchange: 14. Jayson Bukuya 15. Chris Heighington 16. Sam Tagataese 17. Fa’amanu Brown 18. Tony Williams 19. Kurt Capewell 20. Daniel Mortimer 21. Valentine Holmes 
SuperCoach cheapie Jayden Brailey starts at hooker. Recruit Edrick Lee makes his club debut on the wing, with Gerard Beale at fullback in place of Valentine Holmes (hamstring), who has been named in No.21 and is only a slim chance. 
Broncos: 1. Darius Boyd © 2. Corey Oates 3. James Roberts 4. Tautau Moga 5. Jordan Kahu 6. Anthony Milford 7. Ben Hunt 8. Korbin Sims 9. Andrew McCullough 10. Adam Blair 11. Sam Thaiday 12. Matt Gillett 13. Josh McGuire. Interchange: 14. Alex Glenn 15. Tevita Pangai 16. Herman Ese’ese 17. Jai Arrow 18. David Mead 19. Joe Ofahengaue 20. Kodi Nikorima 21. George Fai 
Tautau Moga wins a spot in Brisbane’s backs ahead of David Mead. Jordan Kahu on wing. Broncos also set to go with a four forward bench, with Korbin Sims and Adam Blair starting. media_camera Round 1 NRL teams, 2017. BULLDOGS V STORM 
6pm AEDT Friday, Belmore Sports Ground 
Bulldogs: 1. Will Hopoate 2. Brett Morris 3. Josh Morris 4. Brenko Lee 5. Kerrod Holland 6. Josh Reynolds 7. Moses Mbye 8. Aiden Tolman 9. Michael Lichaa 10. James Graham 11. Josh Jackson 12. Greg Eastwood 13. David Klemmer. Interchange: 14. Sam Kasiano 15. Danny Fualalo 16. Adam Elliott 17. Raymond Faitala-Mariner 19. Francis Tualau 20. Matt Frawley 21. Brad Abbey 23. Craig Garvey 
As predicted, with Brenko Lee and Kerrod Holland joining the backline following the exits of Curtis Rona (French rugby) and Sam Perrett (retired). 
Storm: 1. Young Tonumaipea 2. Suliasi Vunivalu 3. William Chambers 4. Cheyse Blair 5. Josh Addo-Carr 6. Cameron Munster 7. Cooper Cronk 8. Jesse Bromwich 9. Cameron Smith © 10. Jordan McLean 11. Felise Kaufusi 12. Kenny Bromwich 13. Dale Finucane. Interchange: 14. Christian Welch 15. Tim Glasby 16. Nelson Asofa Solomona 17. Brodie Croft 18. Vincent Leuluai 19. Curtis Scott 20. Ryley Jacks 21. Joe Stimson 
Craig Bellamy has opted to keep Cameron Munster at five-eighth, naming Young Tonumaipea at fullback. Brodie Croft is in the first 17. Cheyse Blair wins centre spot over Curtis Scott. RABBITOHS V TIGERS 
8:05pm AEDT Friday, ANZ Stadium 
Rabbitohs: 1. Greg Inglis 2. Alex Johnston 3. Hymel Hunt 4. Siosifa Talakai 5. Bryson Goodwin 6. Cody Walker 7. Luke Kelly 8. Zane Musgrove 9. Robbie Farah 10. David Tyrrell 11. John Sutton 12. Kyle Turner 13. Sam Burgess. Interchange: 14. Damien Cook 15. Jason Clark 16. Thomas Burgess 17. Robert Rochow 18. Angus Crichton 19. Braidon Burns 20. George Burgess 21. Anthony Cherrington 
SuperCoach cheapie Siosifa Talakai scores a centre spot, but Charity Shield revelation Braidon Burns has been relegated to an extended bench. Luke Kelly replaces Adam Reynolds (appendix) at halfback. Popular SuperCoach mid-ranger George Burgess misses the 17. 
Tigers: 1. James Tedesco 2. David Nofoaluma 3. Kevin Naiqama 4. Jamal Idris 5. Jordan Rankin 6. Mitchell Moses 7. Luke Brooks 8. Aaron Woods 9. Matt McIlwrick 10. Ava Seumanufagi 11. Sausao Sue 12. Chris Lawrence 13. Elijah Taylor. Interchange: 14. Tim Grant 15. Josh Aloai 16. Michael Chee-Kham 17. Joel Edwards 18. Jack Littlejohn 19. Justin Hunt 20. JJ Felise 21. Moses Suli 
SuperCoach cheapie Moses Suli misses the 17, named on an extended bench. Popular mid-ranger Jamal Idris scores a starting centre spot. DRAGONS V PANTHERS 
4:30pm AEDT Saturday, UOW Jubilee Oval 
Dragons: 1. Josh Dugan 2. Nene Macdonald 3. Euan Aitken 4. Tim Lafai 5. Jason Nightingale 6. Gareth Widdop 7. Josh McCrone 8. Russell Packer 9. Cameron McInnes 10. Paul Vaughan 11. Tyson Frizell 12. Joel Thompson 13. Jack de Belin. Interchange: 14. Tariq Sims 15. Leeson Ah Mau 16. Jacob Host 17. Jai Field 18. Kurt Mann 19. Taane Milne 20. Jake Marketo 21. Hame Sele. 
Josh McCrone scores the halfback role, with Jai Field named as a bench utility. With Jake Marketo also in the squad, Cameron McInnes is a massive SuperCoach risk. Recruit Paul Vaughan scores a spot at starting prop. 
Panthers: 1. Matt Moylan 2. Dean Whare 3. Waqa Blake 4. Tyrone Peachey 5. Peta Hiku 6. Te Maire Martin 7. Nathan Cleary 8. James Tamou 9. Peter Wallace 10. Reagan Campbell-Gillard 11. Bryce Cartwright 12. Isaah Yeo 13. Trent Merrin. Interchange: 14. James Fisher-Harris 15. Leilani Latu 16. Tim Browne 17. Moses Leota 18. Sitaleki Akauola 19. Dylan Edwards 20. Mitch Rein 21. Sione Katoa 
SuperCoach cheapie Dean Whare returns from an ACL injury on the wing in place of Dallin Watene-Zelezniak (foot, round three), while Peta Hiku earns the other wing spot vacated by Josh Mansour (ACL). Bryce Cartwright reverts to the back row, with youngster Nathan Cleary and Te Marie Martin to play in the halves. Auckland Nines Team of the Tournament member Moses Leota scores the final bench spot and could be a SuperCoach cheapie. COWBOYS V RAIDERS 
7pm AEDT Saturday, 1300SMILES Stadium 
Cowboys: 1. Lachlan Coote 2. Kyle Feldt 3. Justin O’Neill 4. Kane Linnett 5. Antonio Winterstein 6. Michael Morgan 7. Johnathan Thurston (capt) 8. Matt Scott 9. Jack Granville 10. Scott Bolton 11. Gavin Cooper 12. Ethan Lowe 13. Jason Taumalolo. Interchange: 14. Ben Hampton 15. John Asiata 16. Coen Hess 17. Patrick Kaufusi 18. Sam Hoare 19. Gideon Mosby-Gela 20. Javed Bowen 21. Kalyn Ponga 
Shaun Fensom will miss the Round 1 clash against his old team while coach Paul Green is set to give injured winger Antonio Winterstein until Friday to prove his fitness. Says Bowen or Ponga likely to replace him if not fit, despite Gela-Mosby getting jersey No.19 
Raiders: 1. Jack Wighton 2. Nick Cotric 3. Elliott Whitehead 4. Joseph Leilua 5. Jordan Rapana 6. Blake Austin 7. Aidan Sezer 8. Clay Priest 9. Josh Hodgson (capt.) 10. Shannon Boyd 11. Josh Papalii 12. Iosia Soliola 13. Luke Bateman. Interchange: 14. Adam Clydsdale 15. Dunamis Lui 16. Jeff Lima 17 Joseph Tapine 18. Scott Sorenson 19. Zac Santo 20. Makahesi Makatoa 21. Lachlan Croker 
Cheapie Nick Cotric and Elliott Whitehead both in the starting side. TITANS V ROOSTERS 
9pm Saturday AEDT, Cbus Super Stadium 
Titans: 1. Jarryd Hayne 2. Anthony Don 3. Dan Sarginson 4. Konrad Hurrell 5. William Zillman 6. Kane Elgey 7. Ashley Taylor 8. Jarrod Wallace 9. Tyrone Roberts 10. Ryan James (capt) 11. Kevin Proctor (capt) 12. Chris McQueen 13. Leivaha Pulu. Interchange: 14. Karl Lawton 15. Nathanie Peteru 16. Agnatius Paasi 17. Joe Greenwood 18. Paterika Vaivai 19. Matt King 20. Morgan Boyle 21 Tyronne Davis 
Jarrod Wallace will start at prop, with Leivaha Pulu winning the lock spot. Joe Greenwood on bench, with Karl Lawton emerging as a surprise inclusion in the 17 as well. 
Roosters: 1. Michael Gordon 2. Shaun Kenny-Dowall 3. Blake Ferguson 4. Latrell Mitchell 5. Daniel Tupou 6. Luke Keary 7. Mitchell Pearce 8. Jared Waerea-Hargreaves 9. Jake Friend (capt) 10. Dylan Napa 11. Boyd Cordner (capt) 12. Mitchell Aubusson 13. Aidan Guerra. Interchange: 14. Isaac Lui 15. Kane Evans 16. Ryan Matterson 17. Connor Watson 18. Paul Carter 19. Joseph Manu 20. Dale Copley 21. Zane Tetevano 
New signing Michael Gordon starts at fullback with Latrell Mitchell switching to left centre. Connor Watson is the bench utility. WARRIORS V KNIGHTS 
2pm AEDT Sunday, Mt Smart Stadium 
Warriors: 1. Roger Tuivasa-Sheck (C) 2. Tuimoala Lolohea 3. David Fusitu’a 4. Solomone Kata 5. Ken Maumalo 6. Mafoa’aeata Hingano 7. Shaun Johnson 8. Albert Vete 9. Issac Luke 10. Charlie Gubb 11. Bunty Afoa 12. Ryan Hoffman 13. Simon Mannering. Interchange: 14. Erin Clark 15. Jacob Lillyman 16. Sam Lisone 17. Isaiah Papali’i 18. Bodene Thompson 20. Mason Lino 21. James Gavet 22. Blake Ayshford 
Ata Hingano confirmed as Warriors five-eighth for Rd 1 clash with Newcastle. Bunty Afoa starts in the second row. 
Knights: 1. Dylan Phythian 2. Ken Sio 3. Dane Gagai 4. Peter Mata’utia 5. Nathan Ross 6. Brock Lamb 7. Trent Hodkinson 8. Daniel Saifiti 9. Danny Levi 10. Josh Starling 11. Sione Mata’utia 12. Jamie Buhrer 13. Mitch Barnett. Interchange: 14. Luke Yates 15. Jack Stockwell 16. Sam Stone 17. Jacob Saifiti 18. Brendan Elliot 19. Tyler Randell 20. Josh King 21. Anthony Tupou 
Sam Stone and Luke Yates both named on the bench, with Dylan Phythian at fullback. Brock Lamb in the halves. SEA EAGLES V EELS 
4pm Sunday, Brookvale Oval 
Sea Eagles: 1. Tom Trbojevic 2. Jorge Taufua 3. Dylan Walker 4. Brian Kelly 5. Akuila Uate 6. Blake Green 7. Daly Cherry-Evans 8. Brenton Lawrence 9. Apisai Koroisau 10. Martin Taupau 11. Frank Winterstein 12. Curtis Sironen 13. Jake Trbojevic. Interchange: 14. Lewis Brown 15. Nate Myles 16. Addin Fonua-Blake 17. Lloyd Perrett 18. Jarrad Kennedy 19. Cameron Cullen 20. Matthew Wright 21. Jonathan Wright 
SuperCoach cheapie Brian Kelly scores the left centre spot of Steve Matai (retired). Akuila Uate, Frank Winterstein and Lloyd Perrett also loom as cheapie options. Recruit Blake Green forms a new halves combination with Daly Cherry-Evans. 
Eels: 1. Bevan French 2. Semi Radradra 3. Michael Jennings 4. Brad Takairangi 5. Josh Hoffman 6. Clint Gutherson 7. Corey Norman 8. Suaia Matagi 9. Kaysa Pritchard 10. Tim Mannah (c) 11. Manu Ma’u 12. Tepai Moeroa 13. Beau Scott. Interchange: 14. Nathan Brown 15. Daniel Alvaro 16. Rory O’Brien 17. Frank Pritchard 18. Jamal Fogarty 19. Cameron King 20. David Gower 21. Scott Schulte 
Kaysa Pritchard scores the starting hooker role and is now very much in SuperCoach cheapie contention, although Cameron King is also in the squad. Clint Gutherson forms a new-look halves combo with Corey Norman. Recruits Suaia Matagi, Nathan Brown and Frank Pritchard all score spots in the pack.
